    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Feature description\n\nRequesting a builtin support for [`textDocument/selectionRange`][1] LSP feature.\r\n\r\n### What is a selection range?\r\n\r\nFrom the [specification][1] of `selectionRange` request:\r\n> A selection range is a range around the cursor position which the user might be interested in selecting.\r\n\r\nBasically, it returns a range of 'context' around the cursor.\r\n\r\n### How it should be implemented in Neovim\r\n\r\nExposed as API functions inside `vim.lsp.buf` module.  \r\n\r\n1. `selection_range()`: visual select requested range\r\n2. `expand_selection_range()`: visual select parent selection range\r\n3. `selection_range_textobj()`: selection range as a text object (operator-pending mode mapping)\r\n\r\n### Existing Implementations (References)\r\n\r\n- [`nvim-lsp-selection-range`][2] (Neovim plugin written in Lua)\r\n- `Coc.nvim` provides [`<Plug>(coc-range-select)`][3] mapping and a handler ([`src/handler/selectionRange.ts`][4])\r\n\r\n[1]: https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/specifications/lsp/3.17/specification/#textDocument_selectionRange\r\n[2]: https://github.com/camilledejoye/nvim-lsp-selection-range\r\n[3]: https://github.com/neoclide/coc.nvim/blob/43744ba82bd348ea971b87483a13f06f3e46c94b/plugin/coc.vim#L618-L620\r\n[4]: https://github.com/neoclide/coc.nvim/blob/master/src/handler/selectionRange.ts\r\n",
